Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of data mining in software engineering, specifically in generating defect predictors from static code measures. This falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques (differential evolution) to find the best tunings for the data miner, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of hold-out data for testing, which falls under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the implications for changing standard methods in software analytics, which falls under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
